b'A photo is worth a thousand words and a thousand memories. Small business owner Shana Novak built a business out of celebrating those memories through the art of photography. As a New York City based still life photographer, she turns treasured keepsakes and heirlooms into modern art prints. @theheirloomist believes no matter how worn, torn, or odd, your story should be celebrated. We are proud to #SupportSmall by delivering both your heirlooms and your art to your home safely. "For a business that has been around since the 70\'s, FedEx is a totally modern operation in all the ways my business needs it to be. Some days I do my shipping entirely online but when I need a human, they\xe2\x80\x99re only a phone call away. Either way, I need to know that when I send an heirloom or piece of art into the FedEx system, it\'s going to be accounted for and treated well all the way to its destination. Every time, it\'s FedEx for the win." #WorldPhotographyDay \n:camera_with_flash:: @theheirloomist'

b'At FedEx, our people are our strength. Even during these unprecedented times, we are delivering. #TeamFedEx'

b'For 35 years Lenny Vitello has traversed the streets and alleys of lower Manhattan on foot, delivering FedEx packages.

He\xe2\x80\x99s seen just about everything over those years.  He\xe2\x80\x99s steadfastly navigated blackouts, snowstorms, parades, and protests.

But this is different. The coronavirus pandemic is impacting the planet in previously unimagined ways.

To Lenny and our 475,000 team members: Thank you for continuing to deliver for our customers and communities. :purple_heart: :camera:: @steffikeith'

b'How did a FedEx employee deliver a hospital to a suffering child? Trevorn\xe2\x80\x99s vision was severely damaged when a catapulted pencil struck him in the eye. His eyesight remained untreated for years\xe2\x80\x94until Operations Manager Norton Downy leapt into action and fiercely advocated for Trevorn\xe2\x80\x99s laser surgery on the @orbisintl Flying Eye Hospital. Today, Trevorn has a new vision for his future, all #MadePossibleBy Norton. Click the link in our bio to read the full story.'
